<h3>Why Do I Need to Log in with Amazon?</h3>
<p>When you login with Amazon, we collect your email and name registered with it. They are stored in DynamoDB along with the web site list you enter using this website, so that Alexa skill "@ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["AppName"]" can get the list of web sites to check whether they are up or not. DynamoDB is accessible via IAM user credential only, which is stored at this web server but not accessible via http nor https.</p>
